 refers to the action of moving an icon or a window from one location to another on the screen using the mouse. This involves a combination of pressing, holding, and moving the mouse.

**Steps for Dragging:**
1.  Place the pointer over the icon or window you wish to move.
2.  Press and hold down the left mouse button.
3.  While holding the button, move the mouse to the desired new location on the screen.
4.  Release the left mouse button. The icon or window will now be in its new position.

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Place Pointer over Icon/Window] --> B{Press & Hold Left Mouse Button};
    B --> C[Move Mouse to New Location];
    C --> D[Release Left Mouse Button];
    D --> E[Icon/Window Moves];
```
